The paper proposes a method for channel pruning in neural networks for image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training and optimization techniques, which are common in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also introduces sparsity in filters, which is a common technique in neural network compression, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which are common in neural network training, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves pruning techniques, which are common in data compression, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another possible category.
